IApplicationPreloadUtil Interface

Definition

Provides methods that ASP.NET uses to communicate with IIS 7.0 while the server preloads an application.

In this Article

[System.Runtime.InteropServices.Guid("940D8ADD-9E40-4475-9A67-2CDCDF57995C")]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.InterfaceType(System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComInterfaceType.InterfaceIsIUnknown)]
public interface IApplicationPreloadUtil

Methods

GetApplicationPreloadInfo(String,Boolean,String,String[])

Gets initialization data that is required in order to preload an application. This method is called by ASP.NET.

public void GetApplicationPreloadInfo (string context, out bool enabled, out string startupObjType, out string[] parametersForStartupObj);
context
String

The application context.

enabled
Boolean

When this method returns, contains true to indicate that the application has to be preloaded; otherwise, false. This parameter is passed uninitialized.

startupObjType
String

When this method returns, contains a string that identifies the managed type that is part of the preload process. This parameter is passed uninitialized.

parametersForStartupObj
String[]

When this method returns, contains the data that will be passed to the preloaded type. This parameter is passed uninitialized.

ReportApplicationPreloadFailure(String,Int32,String)

Reports that an error occurred in IIS 7.0 while the server was preloading the ASP.NET application.

public void ReportApplicationPreloadFailure (string context, int errorCode, string errorMessage);
context
String

The application context.

errorCode
Int32

The numeric error code.

errorMessage
String

The error text.
